## Executive Summary
A confirmed endpoint compromise was identified on host **win-3450** involving execution of a PowerShell-based attack chain. The activity included:

- Malicious script execution via PowerShell IEX download cradle
- Remote script retrieval from GitHub (known offensive security toolkit)
- Execution of Powercat for reverse shell capability
- Connection to external command-and-control (C2) infrastructure via ngrok
- Evidence of staging and potential data exfiltration activity

This represents an active compromise with remote attacker control over the endpoint.

